  <caaml:metaData>
    <caaml:comment>I dug this pit after a fresh snow fall of 4-7inches.  The snow fell wet and bonded well with the preexisting surface. No major signs of instability were recognizable. A few layers of ice are present within the top 60 cm of the snowpack, however they were not reactive to any stability tests.  The structure of the snow pack seems strong and the strength is relatively good. </caaml:comment>
